From: Michael Olbrich <m.olbrich@pengutronix.de>
Date: Wed, 27 May 2026 16:44:18 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] python: don't install local package with '-e'

For some reason, this causes pip to try to download setuptools, if the
system setuptools (not the one in the ptxdist venv) are too old for pip
itself.

Signed-off-by: Michael Olbrich <m.olbrich@pengutronix.de>
---
 python/scripts/mkvenv.py | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/python/scripts/mkvenv.py b/python/scripts/mkvenv.py
index 8ed6a3545059..f93a170a64d0 100644
--- a/python/scripts/mkvenv.py
+++ b/python/scripts/mkvenv.py
@@ -800,7 +800,7 @@ def _do_ensure(
         env['PIP_CONFIG_SETTINGS'] = "editable_mode=compat"
         pip_install(
             args=["--no-build-isolation",
-                  "-e"] + local_packages,
+                  ] + local_packages,
             online=online,
             wheels_dir=wheels_dir,
             env=env,
